      <para id="id1169316183065">All of the pentahalides undergo thermal decomposition, <link target-id="eip-752"/>. </para>
      
      <equation id="eip-752"><media id="id1169328183861_media" alt="">
            <image mime-type="image/jpg" src="../../media/graphics14-91e7.jpg" id="id1169328183861__onlineimage" width="500" print-width="4.5in"/>
          </media></equation>

<para id="id1169314943282">Careful hydrolysis of the pentahalides yields the oxide of the appropriate trihalide, <link target-id="eip-280"/>, while excess hydrolysis yields phosphoric acid, <link target-id="eip-795"/>. </para>
      
